Sarasota, FL:

That's likely a cyanobacteria bloom, they aren't always green like everyone thinks. There are probably blooms of lyngbya on the bottom as it very popular in Sarasota bay, and definitely looks like oscillatoria mixed in. These toxins can be airborne. https://t.co/NIZN5mgxgI

text: Our sample from Sarasota Bay had BMAA at levels of 8742ug/g, same measurement as ppm. That particular neurotoxin can travel at least 30 miles without dissipating and is linked to ALS, Alzheimers and Parkinsons. . https   twitter com oysterboys941 status 1543981628724240390 photo 1
